---
description: Terminal usage
alwaysApply: true
---

Use the terminal sparingly.

Allowed:

- npm run build
- npm test (only if requested)
- lint (only if requested)
- git status

Avoid:

- repeated builds
- repeated installs
- repeated dev server launches
- unnecessary shell commands

Never rerun commands whose output has already established success.

Only execute commands that directly contribute to solving the task.

When the requested change affects only a few files, avoid searching the entire repository.

Prefer targeted file reads.

Only expand the search if the required implementation cannot be completed from the known context.

After implementation, run:

```bash
npm run build
```

If the build succeeds, stop.

Do not continue experimenting.

Do not perform visual verification unless requested.
